<h3 id=3D"id-09.SD:Overdraft(Arranged&amp;IDOL)LimitsandPricing-Assumptions=
">Assumptions</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 81.=
7247%;">
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 3.34922%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 7.44271%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 79.7243%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 9.52667%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
Ref #</th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
Assumption</th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
Description</th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
Date</th>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A01</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Overdraft limit&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Assume that available balance, overdraft limit and rates are retrieved from=
 10x, and no calculation is required in Customer Portal.&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-07-31" class=3D"date-past">31 Jul 2025</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A02</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Interest&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Assume that all interest calculated to be retrieved from ATLAS, and Custome=
r Portal continues to retrieve interest and transaction information from AT=
LAS.&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-07-31" class=3D"date-past">31 Jul 2025</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A03</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Interest override&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>An account&nbsp;won't have both "above limit" and "within limit" debit i=
nterest overrides simultaneously. While 10x allows an account to have both&=
nbsp;Arranged OD&nbsp;and&nbsp;IDOL, only&nbsp;Arranged OD&nbsp;links to a =
debit interest override =E2=80=94 meaning&nbsp;only one override applies&nb=
sp;at any time.</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-08-26" class=3D"date-past">26 Aug 2025</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A04</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Edge cases handling for closed account</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>For closed accounts, business requirement is to display facilities assoc=
iated with the closed accounts. (INACTIVE facilities)</p><p>The new WASH AP=
I would return only ACTIVE facilities for ACTIVE accounts, and no handling =
is required for the consumer. In the edge case scenario where account is CL=
OSED the WASH endpoint will return only the latest INACTIVE facilities per =
discussion with Ali. (number of facilities to be returned subjected to busi=
ness requirement)&nbsp;</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-10-14" class=3D"date-past">14 Oct 2025</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
