<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p style=3D"text-align: left;"><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>Account Activity Account Details - Arranged and <=
/strong></span></p><p style=3D"text-align: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb=
(0,0,0);"><strong>Intraday Limits</strong></span></p><p style=3D"text-align=
: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">The solution must allow the cus=
tomer to view their Arranged and Intraday limits ($) in the Account Details=
 section (if applicable).</span></p><p style=3D"text-align: left;"><span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">For example, a customer may have:</span></p>
<ol style=3D"text-align: left;">
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Arranged OD and Intraday OD&nbsp;</s=
pan></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Arranged OD only</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Intraday OD only</span></li>
</ol></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">10x</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>To support OD facilities, changes may be requ=
ired across multiple layers of the system architecture. Specifically:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>One Core Arrangement API</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>and<span>&n=
bsp;</span><strong>WASH API</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>may need updates to =
accommodate OD facility data.</li>
<li>The<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>Account Detail EXP API</strong><span>&nbs=
p;</span>should return both the<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>limit for Arrange=
d OD</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>and<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>IDOL</strong>=
<span>&nbsp;</span>for display purposes.</li>
</ul><p>Additionally, there is a consideration to<span>&nbsp;</span><strong=
>split the underlying API</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>responsible for retrie=
ving facility data. This would involve introducing an<span>&nbsp;</span><st=
rong>additional API at the EXP layer</strong>, as well as<strong> additiona=
l API at the</strong> <strong>One Core Arrangement API</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Note:</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>The decision regarding this API=
 split will be finalized<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>after Sprint 4</strong>.=
</p>
</blockquote><p><br></p><p>25 Aug 2025:&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>OD limits</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>will be returned via the<s=
pan>&nbsp;</span><strong>Arrangement Detail endpoint</strong>.</li>
<li>This change introduces<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>additional fields only=
</strong>, with<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>no impact on consuming channels</=
strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Orchestration</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>for OD types and limit=
s will be handled at the<span> <strong>One Core Arrangement API</strong></s=
pan><strong>&nbsp;or WASH API level</strong>, ensuring proper segregation a=
nd data flow.</li>
<li><strong>One Core Arrangement API</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>and<span>&n=
bsp;</span><strong>WASH API </strong>require updates to accommodate OD faci=
lity data.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><p>The<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>Account Detail EXP API</strong><span>&=
nbsp;</span>should return:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Limit for Arranged OD</strong></li>
<li><strong>Limit for IDOL</strong></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>Ac=
count Activity Interest and Tax - Debit Interest</strong></span></p><p><spa=
n style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">The solution must allow the customer to view=
 their overdraft details in the Interest and Tax section with a new heading=
 "Debit Interest", and include the following details:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Debit interest rate: (effective rate=
 %)&nbsp;</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Interest rate type: Variable</span><=
/li>
</ul><p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Business rule</span></st=
rong></p><p style=3D"text-align: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">=
Effective rate is taken from Band 1 for Arranged overdraft&nbsp;</span></p>=
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Unarranag=
ed and Preferential effective rates will not be displayed</span></p><p styl=
e=3D"text-align: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>&nbsp;</=
strong></span></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">10x, WASH API, ATLAS</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Change is required from the<span>&nbsp;</span=
><strong>One Core Arrangement API</strong>, <strong>and&nbsp;the WASH API</=
strong><span>&nbsp;</span>to support arranged/unarranged OD and IDOL intere=
st.</p><h3 id=3D"id-09.SD:Overdraft(Arranged&amp;IDOL)LimitsandPricing-Debi=
tInterestLogic">Debit Interest Logic</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Arranged Overdraft</strong>: Should be treated as<span>&nbsp;</=
span><strong>within limit debit interest</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Unarranged Overdraft</strong>: Should be treated as<span>&nbsp;=
</span><strong>above limit debit interest</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>IDOL Debit Interest Override</strong>: Will also be treated as<=
span>&nbsp;</span><strong>above limit debit interest</strong>.</li>
</ul><h3 id=3D"id-09.SD:Overdraft(Arranged&amp;IDOL)LimitsandPricing-Accoun=
tDetailEXPAPI">Account Detail EXP API</h3>
<ul>
<li>Should return the<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>calculated effective rate</=
strong>.</li>
<li>The only logic in the<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>frontend</strong><span>=
&nbsp;</span>is to display the effective rate from the <strong>within limit=
 debit interest (Arranged Overdraft rate)</strong></li>
<li>Interest should be configured as a flat rate in 10x, so it's not expect=
ed to refer to the interest in tiers/banded.&nbsp;</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
